Remarks . Although we did not examine specimens of
Par. pilosa
from its type locality (Balayan Bay, Luzon I.) or the adjacent area, our specimens from Taiwan and Indonesia agree well with the original description (
Sakai et al . 2006
), including carapace ( Fig. 6A ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: figs. 84, 85), male chelae ( Fig. 6B ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 84), male infraorbital ridges ( Fig. 6C ;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 61), and G1s ( Fig. 6 E–H;
Sakai et al . 2006
: fig. 67).
